Hello,
I have cloned my CMS files locally using
```hs fetch --account=account /```
When I try to run
```‚ùØ hs project create --name FOO
(node:14765) [DEP0040] DeprecationWarning: The `punycode` module is deprecated. Please use a userland alternative instead.
(Use `node --trace-deprecation ...` to show where the warning was created)
[ERROR] Failed fetching release data for latest project.
hs project create

[BETA] Create a new project

Options:
      --version                                   Show version number                                                            [boolean]
  -d, --debug                                     Set log level to debug                                        [boolean] [default: false]
      --help                                      Show help                                                                      [boolean]
  -c, -c, --config                                Path to a config file                                                           [string]
  -p, -a, -p, -a, --portal, --account, --account  HubSpot portal id or name from config                                           [string]
      --name                                      Project name (cannot be changed)                                                [string]
      --location                                  Directory where project should be created                                       [string]
      --template                                  The starting template                                                           [string]
      --templateSource                            Path to custom GitHub repository from which to create project template          [string]
      --use-env                                   Use environment variable config                               [boolean] [default: false]

Examples:
  hs project create  Create a new project```
How do I run the dev server on existing CSM files that have been created through the HubSpot UI?
